    "narrativeText": "FC Richport's greatest UCL triumph arrived in S7 as the club dismantled RB Leipzig, Athletic Club, and Brighton before defeating Manchester City 2–1 in the Final to claim a second Champions League title. Julián Álvarez was the undisputed protagonist — obliterating his own single-season records with 55 goals and 82 contributions, the finest individual season in dynasty history by a considerable margin. The domestic machine remained ruthless: a seventh consecutive Premier League title and an FA Cup completed a True Treble, while Nico Williams' landmark €315.7M sale to Chelsea — the largest in club history — marked the end of an era for the dynasty's original star.",
